        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 11:36PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1136 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles east of Forgan, or 9 miles northeast of Beaver, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Forgan, Knowles, and Mocane.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
